-- Ar Tarim Heads for Record High in Istanbul After Buying Land
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-06-25T10:07:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/ar-tarim-heads-for-record-high-in-istanbul-after-buying-land.html
Ar Tarim Organik Gida AS (ARTOG) , an organic
agriculture company, surged in Istanbul, heading for the highest
level since its listing, after buying farm land in Diyarbakir
province in southeast  Turkey  to expand activities.  Ar Tarim jumped 10 percent to 5.44 liras at the 12:30 p.m.
midday break, almost tripling from its initial public offering
price of 1.89 liras. It started trading on the Istanbul Stock
Exchange on May 31, after selling a 36 percent stake on May 23.  Ankara-based Ar Tarim bought 444,476 square meters of farm
land for 2.69 million liras ($1.5 million), equal to 12 percent
of its total assets at the end of the first quarter, it said in
a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the market
closed on June 22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
